-- Markets situation serious, unprecedented: Merkel
-- 
-- Tue Oct 7, 2008 11:40am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/10/07/us-financial-germany-merkel-idUSTRE4966G520081007

 

 BERLIN  (Reuters) - The situation on financial markets is serious and unprecedented, German Chancellor Angela Merkel said on Tuesday. 

 Speaking at a special session of the Bundestag lower house of parliament devoted to the financial crisis, Merkel said: "The situation on financial markets is serious and has not been seen in this form before." (Reporting by  Iain Rogers )